Resolves: #<issue-number>, #<issue-number>

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# TrimTank Commit Template Instructions (comments are NOT committed)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Allowed and required types:
#
#   feat | fix | docs | refactor | test | chore | perf | ci
#
# Allowed and required scopes (TrimTank architectural layers only):
#
#   cli | server | images | manifest | projects | export | ui
#   docs | tests | package
#
# Rules:
# - Keep the summary line under 72 characters.
# - Keep all body/footer lines under 72 characters.
# - Use imperative mood.
# - Scope must represent the highest architectural layer affected.
# - Never use feature-level scopes (crop-tool, gallery-page, etc.).
# - Include a BREAKING CHANGE footer ONLY if incrementing major version.
# - Only include the Resolves line if closing a GitHub issue number.
#
# Scope guidance:
# - `cli`: command parsing, start command, host/port/dev/verbose
#   behavior, console entry point, and module entry point
# - `server`: FastAPI app, routes, middleware, static file serving,
#   server lifecycle, dev/prod behavior, and HTTP error handling
# - `images`: image discovery, file type filtering, image serving,
#   thumbnailing, Pillow operations, crop processing, EXIF orientation,
#   and output image writing
# - `manifest`: project JSON schema, manifest reads/writes,
#   source-to-output mappings, decisions, crop records, caption records,
#   and manifest migration logic
# - `projects`: project creation/opening, folder structure creation,
#   path resolution, project validation, and project-level settings
# - `export`: training folder export, image/caption pairing, export
#   validation, export records, and training-ready output structure
# - `ui`: web interface, browser-side behavior, Cropper.js integration,
#   gallery, localStorage preferences, mobile layout, and frontend styling
# - `docs`: README and project documentation
# - `tests`: test-only additions or fixes
# - `package`: pyproject.toml, packaging metadata, .gitignore,
#   .gitmessage, dependency declarations, build tooling, and repo config
#
# Scope selection examples:
# - CLI argument changes: `cli`
# - FastAPI route changes: `server`
# - Crop math or saved image output changes: `images`
# - Decision/caption/crop record changes: `manifest`
# - Project folder creation changes: `projects`
# - Training-ready folder generation changes: `export`
# - Browser layout or JavaScript changes: `ui`
# - README changes only: `docs`
# - Test-only changes: `tests`
# - pyproject.toml or repo config changes: `package`
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example commit message:
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# feat(projects): create default dataset folders
#
# Write the standard TrimTank project folders when a user creates a new
# dataset preparation project.
#
# Resolves: #42
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example commit message with breaking change:
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# refactor(manifest): require explicit crop source records
#
# Normalize crop records so every output image can be traced back to a
# source image and crop rectangle.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: existing manifests must add crop source records.
#
